General approach, principles of diagnostics and therapy of malignant tumors. Etiology, symptomatology, diagnosis and principles of therapy of common cancers.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to provide the medial students with the principles of integral approach to malignant tumors, nature and aims of different treatment modalities (surgical oncology, radiotherapy, medical oncology), principles of cancer prophylaxis and early detection , and also with etiology, epidemiology, symptomatology, diagnostics and treatment principles of common malignancies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student
1. Knows the principles of prevention, early detection, diagnostics and treatment of common malignant tumours,
2. Clinical and communication skills;
    a.	is able to obtain anamnesis covering any potential aspects pertaining to a disease;
    b.	is s able to carry out the objective examination of the patient's state of health and fix it in the prescribed medical documentation;
3. Clinical skills
    a.	is able to choose optimal and reasoned examination methods to diagnose a disease;
    b.	is able to interpret the results of diagnostic methods and compose the complete diagnosis of malignant tumors;
    c.	is able to create suitable treatment strategies and follow-up plan.
